  "statement": {
    "markdown": "## Accessible Grid Navigation\n\nIn this challenge, you'll build a grid navigation system that is fully accessible. The system should display a grid of items and allow the user to navigate through the items using only a keyboard. The grid should be responsive and work on different screen sizes.\n\n### Requirements\n\n1. The grid should be laid out using a CSS grid with a 3x3 column and row layout.\n2. The grid items should be accessible via keyboard navigation (up, down, left, right arrow keys).\n3. The items should be announced when selected via screen readers.\n4. The grid should be responsive and work on different screen sizes.\n5. The grid should be styled using Tailwind CSS classes."
  },
